headlines.description: — Gary Trent Jr. beat the buzzer with a long 3-pointer and the Toronto Raptors rallied from a 19-point second-half deficit to beat the Washington Wizards 103-101 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Trent's 3-pointer beats buzzer as Raptors rally past Wizards

events.name: New York Knicks at Brooklyn Nets

headlines.description: — Kyrie Irving scored 40 points, Jeff Green made two free throws with 3.7 seconds left and the Brooklyn Nets overcome the early loss of James Harden to beat the New York Knicks 114-112 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Irving scores 40, Nets lose Harden but beat Knicks 114-112

headlines.description: — Luka Doncic scored 31 points and Dorian Finney-Smith added a season-high 23 as the Dallas Mavericks beat the Utah Jazz 111-103 on Monday night for their season-best fifth straight win.
headlines.shortLinkText: Doncic's 31 points pace Mavs over NBA-leading Jazz 111-103

headlines.description: — D’Angelo Russell scored 25 points in his return from knee surgery and Karl-Anthony Towns had 23 points and 13 rebounds for the Minnesota Timberwolves in a 116-106 win against the Sacramento Kings on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Russell returns with 25 points; Wolves beat Kings 116-106

events.name: Detroit Pistons at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Jerami Grant scored 21 points against his former team, and the Detroit Pistons beat the Oklahoma City Thunder 132-108 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Grant scores 21 vs. former team as Pistons dominate Thunder

events.name: Cleveland Cavaliers at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — Darius Garland scored a career-high 37 points, and the Cleveland Cavaliers beat the San Antonio Spurs 125-101 on Monday night to snap a five-game skid.
headlines.shortLinkText: Garland shines as Cavaliers beat Spurs, end 5-game skid

headlines.description: — Devin Booker scored 18 of his 36 points in the fourth quarter, and the Phoenix Suns beat the Houston Rockets 133-130 on Monday night for their sixth straight win.
headlines.shortLinkText: Booker scores 36 as Suns beat Rockets for 6th straight win
